Function for exploring continuous variables

ExploreCont <- function(x, column){ summary(x[,column]) str(x[,column]) x %>% dplyr::summarise(dfvarDistinctValues = n_distinct(x[,column])) dfvarPlot <- ggplot(data = x, aes(x = x[[column]])) + geom_density() dfvarPlot }

ExploreCont(MIDUS2,“B1SRELCA”)

ExploreCont <- function(x, variable, dfvarDistinctValues, dfvarPlot){ x %>% summary(variable) %>% str(variable) %>% dplyr::summarise(dfvarDistinctValues = n_distinct(variable)) dfvarPlot <- ggplot(data = x, aes(x = variable)) + geom_density() ReturnList <- list(dfvarDistinctValues, dfvarPlot) return(ReturnList) }
